  "instructions": [
    "Heat lard or oil in a donabe over medium heat. Add chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add ground pork and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add nutmeg, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add flour and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add red wine and beef broth, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in sour cream and fermented mustard. Simmer for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve hot over rice or noodles."
